For measuring the light absorption of a VO2 wire with the cross section area (A), the laser beam is focused at the top surface of the tip position of the VO2 wire (point O, Fig. 1a). Considering the 1D steady thermal conduction from the M/I domain wall to the heat sink (the red line section), the I-domain length LI can be expressed as follows according to Fourier’s law19:1LI=ΔT⋅κVO2⋅APa−Rcs⋅κVO2⋅A\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
